Working real hard these days.
Everyday work, cause I am so fucking poor so I have to work sd on one off day. Then 5 days of nursing.
Total I'm having a 6 working day week.
Hai. Like that how!
But that's not what's bugging me.
What's bugging me is that I'm graduating in one month's time!
Yes yes hurray... NOT!
Graduating means the start of a new chapter in my life.
Means I have to go find a fucking job and start my serious adult life at the tender age of 20!!!!
How sia.
I am very very very scared of the future.
I am a very live-in-the-past person!
I just wanna have fun.
But nursing is soooo serious!
I loveeee talking and making friends and hanging out with new people!
But from what I see, nurses are awesome poker players! Cause everyone puts on a pokerface when yet go to work.
They may laugh with you but any problem, they will be the first to point at you.
Life, a big sigh.

I want to live in a gay world, can I?


Ps: seriously you're like the cutest nurse!
